OL,3,C'Evil' domestic abuser who murdered
OL,4,Cpartner 'should have been stopped'
OL,6,FBut a series of measures should have
OL,7,Falready been in place to prevent Keel
OL,8,Ffrom killing.
OL,10,FAfter his previous convictions, he had
OL,11,Fbeen enrolled in a behavioural
OL,12,Fprogramme for domestic abusers, but we
OL,13,Fcan now report he was not turning up -
OL,14,Fregularly missing the rehabilitation
OL,15,Fappointments.
OL,17,FHis attendance was described as
OL,18,F"sporadic", despite being deemed a
OL,19,F"high risk offender".
